.TH ULTIMATE-LINUX-SUITE 1 "December 2025" "ultimate-linux-suite 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ultimate-linux-suite \- Comprehensive Linux system management toolkit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ultimate-linux-suite
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Ultimate Linux Suite is a script-only, clone-and-run Linux toolkit providing
unified system management across multiple distributions. It offers a
comprehensive set of tools for application installation, driver management,
system optimization, and recovery operations.
.PP
The suite provides:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-distro package management abstraction
.IP \(bu 2
Queue-based operation system for staged changes
.IP \(bu 2
60+ application installer with cross-distro mapping
.IP \(bu 2
System optimization (ZRAM, THP, BBR, swappiness tuning)
.IP \(bu 2
Driver management (NVIDIA, AMD, Intel, Broadcom Wi-Fi)
.IP \(bu 2
Recovery tools (DNS reset, orphan cleanup, package repair)
.IP \(bu 2
Comprehensive hardware and OS detection
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debug output for troubleshooting
.SH MODULES
.TP
.B Apps
Install recommended applications from a curated database of 60+ cross-platform packages
.TP
.B Drivers
Manage hardware drivers including graphics (NVIDIA, AMD, Intel) and wireless (Broadcom, Realtek)
.TP
.B Optimization
System performance tuning including memory management, I/O schedulers, and kernel parameters
.TP
.B Recovery
System repair tools for package management issues, DNS problems, and orphaned packages
.TP
.B Profiles
Quick setup profiles for common use cases (workstation, gaming, server, developer, pentesting)
.SH SUPPORTED DISTRIBUTIONS
.TP
.B Arch-based
Arch Linux, Manjaro, EndeavourOS, ArcoLinux
.TP
.B Debian-based
Debian, Ubuntu, Linux Mint, Pop!_OS, elementary OS
.TP
.B Fedora-based
Fedora, RHEL, CentOS, Rocky Linux, AlmaLinux
.TP
.B openSUSE
openSUSE Leap, openSUSE Tumbleweed
.TP
.B Security Distros
Kali Linux, Parrot OS
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Launch interactive menu:
.RS
sudo ultimate-linux-suite
.RE
.TP
.B Show version:
.RS
ultimate-linux-suite --version
.RE
.TP
.B Enable debug mode:
.RS
sudo ultimate-linux-suite --debug
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/share/ultimate-linux-suite/
Main installation directory containing all scripts and modules
.TP
.B /usr/share/ultimate-linux-suite/configs/
Configuration files including app presets and optimization profiles
.TP
.B /usr/share/ultimate-linux-suite/drivers/
Driver-specific installation scripts and documentation
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Required
bash (>= 4.0), gawk
.TP
.B Recommended
pciutils, usbutils, dmidecode, smartmontools, lsb-release
.TP
.B Optional
flatpak, snapd (for additional package manager support)
.SH NOTES
Many operations require root privileges and will modify system configuration.
Always review queued operations before confirming execution.
.PP
The suite uses a queue-based system to stage multiple operations before
executing them, allowing you to review and modify planned changes.
